cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SD

This paper is about using language modeling pre-training and transfer learning to overcome the challenge of data scarcity in task-oriented dialogue systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses decision making and reasoning, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
